Japan Reports 342 Fault Lines Near Nuclear Plants, Yomiuri Says

-- B y   Y u j i   O k a d a
-- 
2011-06-01T06:08:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/japan-reports-342-fault-lines-near-nuclear-plants-yomiuri-says.html
Japan ’s nuclear safety agency
received 342 reports of geological fault lines near nuclear
plants from 12 companies operating atomic facilities, including
power generators, the Yomiuri newspaper said.  The tectonic faults aren’t recognized as active and the
agency plans to investigate whether they need to be taken into
consideration in designing nuclear power plants, the paper said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Yuji Okada in  Tokyo  at 
 yokada6@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
